  "notes": [
    "Preference will be given to junior-level applicants with the highest grades overall who have satisfactorily completed the following required course work. Required for admission : Students must have a cumulative UC transferable GPA of 3.0 (3.4 for TAG) One course in statistics equivalent to UCI's STATS 7 with a grade of B- or better Important: Articulation of General Chemistry is based on the completion of the entire year. Students wishing information on course-to-course equivalencies (semester to quarter) should contact the Physical Sciences Student Affairs Office at: pssazot@uci.edu. NOTE : In fulfillment of the requirements below, a single course may be used only once. For information regarding the AP and IB examination credit policies refer to the UCI General Catalogue. For more information regarding the UC Irvine Transfer Admission Guarantee Program, please visit TAG"
